objectives:
In large institutions, many workflows are based on physical documents that circulate among many members of the organization, traditionally requiring a physical signature. The digitalization and virtualization of documental workflows provide an efficient way to decouple organizations from physical constraints and enable a flexible and dynamic management of documentation, facilitating solutions of working at home or at distance and enabling the development of virtual team collaboration.

As it is well known, physical signing of documents can be easily replaced by digital signatures, based either on physical tokens (ID cards, personal certificates) or other e-ID solutions. Unhappily, digital certified signatures require a cumbersome and often slow process of opening a document, checking its nature, and digital signing by introduction of a code (or another digital signature method) on a one by one basis. In this sense, the virtual process is sometimes slower that the physical counterpart, since there is still no easy way of opening a large set of documents and making an overall check of the whole set. While it is easy to perform such tasks in small scale, for managers on top of large organizations, who may have to deal daily with dozens or even hundreds of digital signatures, such process becomes easily unmanageable and inefficient.

SmartSigner https://smartsigner.eu/ is a solution developed in-house by Instituto Superior Técnico to facilitate the process of signing electronic documents and tackle some of the issues that arise from the transition of an organization into the digital era. The current implementation of SmartSigner already provides a large set of 
features such as:

   - distributed document management;
   - batch signing;
   - support for Portugal's CEGER signing certificate;
   - basic support for signing with the national Citizen Card;
   - an API for external application integrations;
   - "printable" signed electronic documents with mechanisms that allow
the holder to obtain a printable version of the digitally signed document;

Smart Signer is already successfully used today in several critical IST workflow processes that require legally binding digital signatures.

However, many other features are still lacking on the overall solution, namely support for several digital signature solutions that are available today in Portuguese and EU legal landscape.

The goal of this dissertation is to analyze, develop and implement in a real world scenario extensions and new applications to the Smart Signer infrastructure, including namely:
-	Full support of digital signature using the Portuguese Citizen Card;
-	Full support of signatures based on Digital Mobile Key (Chave Móvel Digital);
-	Integration of professional attributes;
-	Generic plugable support for other signing certificates;
-	Integration for signing with HSM based solutions;
-	Document "re-signing" to prolong it's validity.

The work will comprise the following steps:

1.	Review the state of the art of digital signing solutions;
2.	Survey of existing technologies and tools for digital signing solutions;
3.	Analysis and implementation of a prototype system for digital signing using national eID cards;
4.	Integration of developed prototype solutions in the SmartSigner platform; 
5.	Test and assessment of developed solutions;
6.	Discussion and conclusion.

